metadata.name: Cuddles
metadata.description:
Financial markets and bunnies,
Such strange and diverse beasts,
One driven by numbers and gain,
The other by carrots and feasts.

But both can bring joy and despair,
With their highs and their lows,
The markets with their booms and busts,
The bunnies with their fluffy noses.

Oh, how they can both perplex us,
These creatures so unlike our own,
But still they capture our hearts and minds,
And leave us feeling all alone.

So let us embrace their mysteries,
And revel in their endless surprise,
For in the end, they both bring us joy,
And help us reach for the skies.
